# File Upload System

Portal provides comprehensive file upload capabilities with S3/R2 integration, progress tracking, and secure handling.

## Architecture

### Core Components
- `app/api/upload/route.ts`: S3 pre-signed URL generation API endpoint
- `hooks/use-upload.ts`: React hook for file uploads with progress tracking
- `lib/s3.ts`: S3/R2 client configuration and utilities
- `components/shared/attachment-preview.tsx`: File attachment preview component

### Upload Flow
1. Client requests pre-signed URL from `/api/upload`
2. Server generates unique filename and S3 pre-signed URL
3. Client uploads directly to S3 using pre-signed URL
4. Progress tracking and error handling via custom hook
5. Success callback with file key for database storage

## API Endpoint

### Pre-signed URL Generation
```typescript
// app/api/upload/route.ts
export async function POST(request: Request) {
  const { filename, contentType } = await request.json();
  
  // Generate unique filename
  const extension = filename.split('.').pop();
  const uniqueFilename = `${randomString(10)}.${extension}`;
  
  // Create S3 pre-signed URL
  const signedUrl = await getSignedUrl(
    s3,
    new PutObjectCommand({
      Bucket: env.S3_BUCKET_NAME,
      Key: uniqueFilename,
      ContentType: contentType,
    }),
    { expiresIn: 60 } // 1 minute expiry
  );
  
  return NextResponse.json({
    url: signedUrl,
    key: uniqueFilename,
  });
}
```

### Request/Response Format
```typescript
// Request
{
  filename: string;
  contentType: string;
}

// Response
{
  url: string;      // Pre-signed upload URL
  key: string;      // Unique file key for storage
}
```

## S3 Configuration

### Client Setup
```typescript
// lib/s3.ts
import { S3Client } from '@aws-sdk/client-s3';

export const s3 = new S3Client({
  region: env.S3_REGION,
  endpoint: env.S3_ENDPOINT,
  credentials: {
    accessKeyId: env.S3_ACCESS_KEY_ID,
    secretAccessKey: env.S3_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY,
  },
  forcePathStyle: true, // Required for R2 compatibility
});
```

### Environment Variables
```bash
S3_BUCKET_NAME=your-bucket-name
S3_REGION=auto
S3_ENDPOINT=https://your-account.r2.cloudflarestorage.com
S3_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-access-key
S3_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-secret-key
```

## Upload Hook

### useUpload Hook Implementation
```typescript
interface UseUploadOptions {
  onSuccess?: (key: string) => void;
  onError?: (error: Error) => void;
  onProgress?: (info: string) => void;
}

export function useUpload(options: UseUploadOptions = {}) {
  const [isUploading, setIsUploading] = useState(false);

  const uploadToS3 = async (data: Blob | File) => {
    try {
      setIsUploading(true);
      options.onProgress?.('Uploading file to S3...');

      // Get pre-signed URL
      const response = await ky
        .post<{ url: string; key: string }>('/api/upload', {
          json: {
            filename: data instanceof File ? data.name : 'no-name',
            contentType: data.type || 'application/octet-stream',
          },
        })
        .json();

      // Upload directly to S3
      const uploadResponse = await ky.put(response.url, {
        body: data,
        headers: {
          'Content-Type': data.type || 'application/octet-stream',
        },
      });

      if (!uploadResponse.ok) {
        throw new Error(`Upload failed with status: ${uploadResponse.status}`);
      }

      options.onProgress?.(`File uploaded: ${response.key}`);
      options.onSuccess?.(response.key);
      
      return response.key;
    } catch (error) {
      const errorMessage = error instanceof Error ? error.message : 'Unknown upload error';
      options.onProgress?.(`Upload error: ${errorMessage}`);
      options.onError?.(error instanceof Error ? error : new Error(errorMessage));
      throw error;
    } finally {
      setIsUploading(false);
    }
  };

  return {
    uploadToR2: uploadToS3, // Alias for backward compatibility
    isUploading,
  };
}
```

### Hook Usage Examples
```tsx
// Basic usage
export function FileUploadComponent() {
  const { uploadToR2, isUploading } = useUpload({
    onSuccess: (key) => {
      console.log('File uploaded successfully:', key);
      // Save key to database via tRPC
    },
    onError: (error) => {
      console.error('Upload failed:', error);
      toast.error('Failed to upload file');
    },
    onProgress: (info) => {
      console.log('Upload progress:', info);
    },
  });

  const handleFileSelect = async (event: ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) => {
    const file = event.target.files?.[0];
    if (file) {
      try {
        const fileKey = await uploadToR2(file);
        // Handle successful upload
      } catch (error) {
        // Error already handled in hook
      }
    }
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <input
        type="file"
        onChange={handleFileSelect}
        disabled={isUploading}
      />
      {isUploading && <p>Uploading...</p>}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## File Preview Component

### Attachment Preview
```tsx
interface AttachmentPreviewProps {
  fileKey: string;
  fileName: string;
  fileSize?: number;
  contentType?: string;
  onRemove?: () => void;
}

export function AttachmentPreview({
  fileKey,
  fileName,
  fileSize,
  contentType,
  onRemove,
}: AttachmentPreviewProps) {
  const fileUrl = `${env.NEXT_PUBLIC_S3_PUBLIC_URL}/${fileKey}`;
  
  const isImage = contentType?.startsWith('image/');
  
  return (
    <div className="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 border rounded-lg">
      {isImage ? (
        <img
          src={fileUrl}
          alt={fileName}
          className="w-12 h-12 object-cover rounded"
        />
      ) : (
        <FileIcon className="w-12 h-12 text-muted-foreground" />
      )}
      
      <div className="flex-1">
        <p className="font-medium">{fileName}</p>
        {fileSize && (
          <p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            {formatFileSize(fileSize)}
          </p>
        )}
      </div>
      
      <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
        <Button variant="outline" size="sm" asChild>
          <a href={fileUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <ExternalLinkIcon className="w-4 h-4" />
          </a>
        </Button>
        
        {onRemove && (
          <Button
            variant="outline"
            size="sm"
            onClick={onRemove}
          >
            <XIcon className="w-4 h-4" />
          </Button>
        )}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Integration Patterns

### Database Storage
Store file metadata in database after successful upload:

```typescript
// tRPC mutation for saving file metadata
export const uploadFile = protectedProcedure
  .input(z.object({
    fileKey: z.string(),
    fileName: z.string(),
    fileSize: z.number(),
    contentType: z.string(),
    relatedEntityId: z.string().optional(),
    relatedEntityType: z.string().optional(),
  }))
  .mutation(async ({ ctx, input }) => {
    const fileRecord = await ctx.db.insert(fileAttachment).values({
      id: crypto.randomUUID(),
      userId: ctx.session.user.id,
      fileKey: input.fileKey,
      fileName: input.fileName,
      fileSize: input.fileSize,
      contentType: input.contentType,
      relatedEntityId: input.relatedEntityId,
      relatedEntityType: input.relatedEntityType,
      createdAt: new Date(),
    });
    
    return fileRecord;
  });
```

### Form Integration
```tsx
export function ContactFormWithFiles() {
  const form = useForm<ContactFormData>({
    resolver: zodResolver(contactSchema),
  });
  
  const [attachments, setAttachments] = useState<FileAttachment[]>([]);
  
  const { uploadToR2, isUploading } = useUpload({
    onSuccess: (key) => {
      // Add to attachments list
      setAttachments(prev => [...prev, { key, name: file.name }]);
    },
  });

  const onSubmit = async (data: ContactFormData) => {
    // Include attachment keys in form submission
    await createContact.mutateAsync({
      ...data,
      attachments: attachments.map(a => a.key),
    });
  };

  return (
    <Form {...form}>
      {/* Form fields */}
      
      <FormField
        control={form.control}
        name="attachments"
        render={() => (
          <FormItem>
            <FormLabel>Attachments</FormLabel>
            <FormControl>
              <FileUploadZone
                onFilesSelected={handleFilesSelected}
                isUploading={isUploading}
              />
            </FormControl>
            
            {attachments.map((attachment) => (
              <AttachmentPreview
                key={attachment.key}
                {...attachment}
                onRemove={() => removeAttachment(attachment.key)}
              />
            ))}
          </FormItem>
        )}
      />
    </Form>
  );
}
```

## Security Considerations

### Pre-signed URL Security
- Short expiration time (1 minute) for upload URLs
- Unique filename generation to prevent overwrites
- Content-Type validation on both client and server
- File size limits enforced at S3 level

### Access Control
- Authentication required for pre-signed URL generation
- User-based file access through database relations
- Private S3 bucket with controlled public access
- Audit logging for all file operations

## Best Practices

### File Naming
- Generate unique filenames to prevent conflicts
- Preserve original file extensions
- Use secure random string generation
- Avoid user-provided filenames in storage keys

### Error Handling
- Comprehensive error messages for debugging
- Graceful degradation for upload failures
- Progress feedback for long uploads
- Retry mechanisms for network failures

### Performance
- Direct S3 upload to reduce server load
- Progress tracking for user feedback  
- Lazy loading for file previews
- Efficient file metadata queries

### Cleanup
- Implement garbage collection for orphaned files
- Remove files when related entities are deleted
- Monitor storage usage and costs
- Automatic cleanup of temporary uploads